tasks.content: Now we will create our first application in Experience Builder (EB for short). To do this, select "Create App" (1), and then choose "Experience Builder" (2).
Now we have moved on to your Experience Builder app. Next, select "Create new" (3). Every time you want to create an app, you will need to do it here.

Now the application asks us to choose a template for our app. In reality, you can always change it later if needed. For now, we are selecting a fixed template, which is characterized by taking up the entire screen of the computer. We choose BlankFullscreen and then click "Create" (4).

Let's change the name of our application to "Ski Resort" (5). To do this, click on the "Untitled experience" text and then type "Ski Resort". Now, let's add a header to do this, toggle the switch (6).
Click "Edit Header" (7), then select "Choose a header template" (8), and choose "Header 1" (9).

Now our header has been added. You can modify it in the panel on the right side (10). However, we will now move to the **Pages** section (11) in the left panel, and then proceed to add a new page (12).

Now we will add another page to our application by clicking "Blank Fullscreen" (13). Notice that our application now consists of two pages. Since you already know how to add a header, please add a header to the newly created page as well.

To add a header, click (14). Notice that now we have two pages, which you can see in the "Pages" panel (15). Even more interestingly, we also have two pages visible in the header (16): "Pages" and "Pages 2". The fact that we can create a multi-page application is one of the features that sets Experience Builder (EB) apart from what Web App Builder offered.
Let's make our page names more readable (17). Click (...), select "Rename page", and rename the first page to "Home". Then rename the second page to "Slope Data".

Leave the application with the updated page names as shown in step (18). Now, we will focus on adding data to our application. It's important that you have already configured your Web Map based on the video from 6. Lecture: Web Map Configuration.
When finishing work, make sure you save the changes by clicking on the disk icon (19), otherwise your changes may simply disappear when the page is refreshed without being saved first.
